com.cse110team24.walkwalkrevolution.firebase.firestore.adapters

Class FireBaseFireStoreAdapterTeams

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cse110team24.walkwalkrevolution.firebase.firestore.adapters.FireBaseFireStoreAdapterTeams
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DatabaseService, TeamsDatabaseService, TeamsDatabaseServiceSubject, Subject<TeamsDatabaseServiceObserver>

    public class FireBaseFireStoreAdapterTeams
extends java.lang.Object
implements TeamsDatabaseService
    This type's database provider is Cloud Firestore. The document path for a team is teams/\{team\}. The document path for a teammate is teams/{\team\}/teammates/\{teammate}. The document path for a teammate route is teams/{\team\}/routes/\{route}.

      • getUserTeam

        public void getUserTeam(java.lang.String teamUid,
                        java.lang.String currentUserDisplayName)
        Description copied from interface: TeamsDatabaseService
        Query this service's provider database for the teammates in the specified team document. All teammates' data are returned except the currently signed in user's.

        On complete, a call to TeamsDatabaseServiceSubject.notifyObserversTeamRetrieved(ITeam) is made to notify observers that the team is ready.

        Specified by:
        getUserTeam in interface TeamsDatabaseService
        Parameters:
        teamUid - the already-existing team's ID
        currentUserDisplayName - the currently signed-in user's displayName

      • getUserTeamRoutes

        public void getUserTeamRoutes(java.lang.String teamUid,
                              java.lang.String currentUserDisplay,
                              int routeLimitCount,
                              com.google.firebase.firestore.DocumentSnapshot lastRoute)
        Description copied from interface: TeamsDatabaseService
        Query this service's provider database for the routes in the specified team document, limited by the amount of routes requested. All teammates's routes are given except those of the currently signed in user.

        On complete, a call to TeamsDatabaseServiceSubject.notifyObserversTeamRoutesRetrieved(List, DocumentSnapshot) is made containing up to the amount of requested routes and a DocumentSnapshot to the last document retrieved.

        Specified by:
        getUserTeamRoutes in interface TeamsDatabaseService
        Parameters:
        teamUid - the already-existing team's ID
        currentUserDisplay - the currently signed in user's display name.
        routeLimitCount - the amount of routes to Query the database for. List of routes may be <= this number.
        lastRoute - the last retrieved route's document, used to determine where to start querying this service's provider database from given the last request. Should be null if ruquesting routes for the first time.
